        "verse_ref": "",
        "content": "And as Moses lifted up the serpent in the wilderness, even so\nmust the Son of man be lifted up: that whosoever believeth in\nhim should not perish, but have eternal life. John 3:14, 15.\nI point you to the cross of Calvary. I ask you to consider the\ninfinite sacrifice made in your behalf that through faith in Jesus\nChrist you may not perish but have everlasting life.... I point you to\nJesus. You are safe in committing to Him the innermost working\nof your mind. The Lord Jesus hath purchased you with an infinite\nprice. You may commit the keeping of your soul to Jesus. You may\ntrust Him as your Counselor.... Constantly draw nigh unto God. He\nwill help you.\nO be sure you receive your illumination from the Source of\nall light. He is the great central Light of the universe of heaven\nand the great Light of the world. He will enlighten every man that\ncometh into the world. Reach no cheap, low standard. Cultivate\nthe gentleness of Christ. Secure the highest attainments, and draw\nyour inspiration from Jesus Christ. He is your Friend. You may\nalways depend upon Him and find Him faithful and true. When\nyou need His sympathy in your greatest perplexity, wounded and\nbruised, He will not pass you by on the other side. To Him you may\ncome in the simplicity of children. To Him you may come with joy\nand rejoicing. With everything that is flattering to your hopes, every\nsuccess which attends your labors in the Lord, look up to Jesus and\nlay every honor at His feet. Everything depends upon your walking\nin all humility of mind. Write the name of Christ upon your banner\nand never dishonor your colors.\nAll heaven was given to us in Christ Jesus.... O honor Jesus by\ngiving to Him the heart’s best and holiest services! He has given His\nlife for you. Who is He that hath done this? The only begotten Son\nof God, He that was One with the Father before the world was.\nExaltingtheManofCalvary,December1 707\nLift up your banner, lift it up higher. Never, never let it trail in\nthe dust of the earth. Exalt Jesus. Lift Him up, the Man of Calvary,\nhigher and still higher.1\n1Letter147,1896."
